
[1]cleavage

   CLEAVAGE, n.

   1. The act of cleaving or splitting.

   2. In mineralogy, the manner of cleaving, or of mechanical division. It
   is used in relation to the fracture of minerals which have natural
   joints and possess a regular structure.
